reviews.text: Looking for the beachfront place to chill with friends and hungry kids? Keep looking. Waiting time is beyond expectation - more then an hour for 5 kids burgers with French fries. One lost order. One very bad Mochito .. one star for the location and view. One star “not bad food” (but overpriced) .  Try Long Island nearby if you’re already there anyway- good Asian fusion menu, decent service.

Best place to have a blissful day at the beach and enjoy with friends and family. Good food selection served by friendly staff who never fails to put a smile on your face! Would definitely keep coming back!
Nice view, nice food and drinks!
Fabulous food, great drinks and super service. View and setting is wonderful

Food reasonable. So not a problem there. We were on the way to Longisland having seen the better review and scores, but were impressed and attracted by the layout/presentation.

Service was not super rude or bad. Just had an air of superiority and “what are you talking about?”

Eg: “I would like a Fever Tree Ginger Beer” (pointing at this item on the menu”

Lady brings what looks like Tonic Water...

“yeah we wanted fever tree ginger beer”

“yeah this is fever tree, tonic water, we dont have ginger beer”

Before the “but it's there on the menu and I was point to it” was even forming on my lips, she had turned away.

I mean WTH...
